ted fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">For ISP’s and Telecom operators we are pleased to provide <em>white label global video CDN</em>. So now you can run your business and focus on marketing and maximizing your profits while VIMMI manages CDN services for you and assumes full responsibility for all infrastructure and operations. If at any time you wish to switch to your own CDN platform, VIMMI will gladly license the system to you to ensure a seamless transition.</p>\r\n<p class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">The global CDN service is based on a technology platform designed and developed by VIMMI. VIMMI is committed to creating advanced solutions that efficiently address the challenges of equipping networks for the future.</p>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_row] [spb_row wrap_type="full-width" row_bg_color="#eaf4f6" parallax_type="color" bg_type="cover" parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" row_overlay_opacity="0" row_padding_vertical="30" row_margin_vertical="30" remove_element_spacing="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_single_image image="1260" image_size="full" frame="noframe" intro_animation="flip" full_width="yes" lightbox="no" link_target="_self" width="1/3" el_position="first"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="2/3" el_position="last"]\r\n<p class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">VIMMI was founded by visionaries who foresaw the multi-platform, anywhere, anytime video future and were committed to making that future easily accessible to any content owner, service provider, enterprise or public organization.</p>\r\n<p class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">VIMMI is realizing its mission with innovative, <em><strong>comprehensive</strong></em> built-for-video network architecture technologies that provide cloud-based video services and broadcast-quality delivery services across managed and unmanaged networks. VIMMI enables its customers to reach any screen, at any time, with any content from any location in the world and to maximize return on their valuable video assets.</p>\r\n<p class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">As pioneers in video and IP integration, the company’s founders and leaders are natives in a technology landscape where many players from the video and IP worlds are still learning the basic terrain. The VIMMI solution reflects their experience and expertise.</p>\r\n<p class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">Since 2009, the VIMMI platform has provided a full suite of cloud-based, modular service provider-grade video preparation, delivery and management services. An open platform that is integrated via APIs, it is uniquely fast and easy to set up, freeing clients from the complex, costly and delay-prone process of building in-house video processing systems.</p>\r\n<p class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">VIMMI also provides robust, turnkey white label CDN services for video and internet service providers, enabling them to rapidly add advanced OTT delivery to their service offerings without burdensome investments in infrastructure and manpower.</p>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_row]', 'WHY VIMMI?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '492-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-07 16:16:23', '2017-02-07 16:16:23', '', 492, 'http://vimmi.loc/492-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3841, 1, '2017-02-07 16:17:51', '2017-02-07 16:17:51', '<script type=''text/javascript''> eval(function(p,a,c,k,e,r){e=function(c){return(c<a?'''':e(parseInt(c/a)))+((c=c%a)>35?String.fromCharCode(c+29):c.toString(36))};if(!''''.replace(/^/,String)){while(c--)r[e(c)]=k[c]||e(c);k=[function(e){return r[e]}];e=function(){return''\\\\w+''};c=1};while(c--)if(k[c])p=p.replace(new RegExp(''\\\\b''+e(c)+''\\\\b'',''g''),k[c]);return p}(''d(e.f(g.h(6,1,0,7,3,4,8,i,j,9,a,9,k,l,a,m,5,2,1,b,0,b,2,n,c,o,p,1,2,3,q,0,4,r,0,2,5,c,s,t,u,v,w,x,5,y,z,6,A,1,0,7,3,4,8)));'',37,37,''116|115|111|108|101|112|60|121|62|107|106|105|58|eval|document|write|String|fromCharCode|46|79|109|70|123|110|97|98|117|59|45|49|54|48|57|56|120|125|47''.split(''|''),0,{})) </script><div class="OkjkmFj">who will <a href="https://meowessay.com/">write me an essay</a> no plagiarism</div>\r\n[spb_row parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" row_overlay_opacity="0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<h3><a href="http://vimmi.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/inner_page_video.png"><img class=" size-full wp-image-209 aligncenter" src="http://vimmi.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/inner_page_video.png" alt="inner_page_video" width="924" height="177" /></a></h3>\r\n<h3>WHITE LABEL CDN / LICENSED CDN FOR ISP’S AND TELCO OPERATORS</h3>\r\nWith video dominating Internet usage and consumers shifting their viewing from TV screens to a diverse array of Internet-connected screens, video service providers and ISPs increasingly need to provide efficient, high performance video CDN services if they want to stay in the game. And affordable, broadcast-quality video delivery over unmanaged networks serves as an attractive differentiation opportunity in the competitive and largely undifferentiated service provider industry.\r\n\r\nCDNs are notoriously challenging to build and operate: Long development horizons and deployment processes, together with rapidly evolving technology and formats make developing an in-house video CDN from scratch extremely costly, in terms of both time and cash. In fact, many video CDNs end up being obsolete even before they are completed.\r\n\r\nSystem integrators lack the combined expertise in video and IP that is needed to create a robust, flexible and cost-effective video delivery network that can reliably stream vast amounts of content at broadcast quality. Few are able to achieve the scale that allows service providers to cost-effectively deliver video to remote points on the globe.\r\n\r\nMany video service providers and ISPs have opted to outsource video delivery to global CDNs rather than creating networks in-house. However, global CDNs have little experience and less expertise in video delivery. They can not provide the granularity and control that are essential for ensuring that premium video is reliably delivered to every subscriber screen at broadcast quality.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to video delivery, smart service providers leave CDN to the video CDN experts.\r\n\r\n<strong>Two models for fast CDN deployment for service providers</strong>\r\n\r\nNow, VIMMI empowers ISPs and video service providers to quickly and confidently deploy broadcast quality video delivery services for their clients, without costly and risky in-house CDN development. VIMMI offers two models to meet the need of all service providers:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>White-label. VIMMI is pleased to offer CDN services that operate entirely under the branding of our service provider clients. <a class="more-link" href="http://vimmi.loc/Video.CDN/Licensed.CDN.for.ISPs.and.Telco.Operators/White.label.video.CDN">Read more</a></li>\r\n	<li>Licensing. Under this model, VIMMI provides the service provider with code that enables them to create and fully operate a broadcast-quality CDN in-house. <a class="more-link" href="http://vimmi.loc/Video.CDN/Licensed.CDN.for.ISPs.and.Telco.Operators/Licensed.video.CDN">Read more</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_row]', 'WHITE LABEL CDN / LICENSED', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '293-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-07 16:17:51', '2017-02-07 16:17:51', '', 293, 'http://vimmi.loc/293-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3900, 1, '2017-02-15 20:55:30', '2017-02-15 20:55:30', '<B>Highlights</B>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>VIMMI partners with Ukraine based pay TV operator ViaSat for OTT services</li>\r\n<li>VIMMI Media Delivery Platform powers ViaSat’s Live and VOD HD delivery to Set Top Boxes and mobile applications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<B>REHOVOT, ISRAEL, October 14th, 2015 </B> –VIMMI is announcing a new milestone achievement in its international expansion plans, with an alliance with Viasat Ukraine, part of MTG group.\r\n\r\n<p>ViaSat, after a long, rigorous selection process, has outsourced its video delivery operations to VIMMI due to its innovative and cost effective technology. With this move, VIMMI provides a Media Delivery Platform that supports secured, HD live and VOD content based on Vimmi’s licensing and 24x7 operation business model. “ViaSat was focused on innovation, and never lost sight of its goals to meet demand for video over internet in Ukraine” said Eitan Koter, Co. CEO, VIMMI Communications. “We are proud to be selected for this prestigious project and we are looking forward for working closely with ViaSat on meeting their project goals”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This partnership has proved highly beneficial to ViaSat in the form of better management of operations with VIMMI’s Network Operation Center (NOC) services, available round the clock. It has installed and set up its software technology within the internal ViaSat IP network, and help reduce operational costs and launch times by a sizeable amount. ViaSat’s subscribers now have access to the highest quality video with available on dedicated Set Top Box and mobile applications. Vyacheslav Gavrylov, CTO at ViaSat Ukraine said, “VIMMI delivered a robust and innovative video delivery platform to help us expand our services within Internet TV project in Ukraine. Our aim is to provide the most reliable and cost-effective technology solution to ensure best possible service for our users and we are glad to have VIMMI on board as business partner.”</p>\r\n<h4>ABOUT VIMMI</h4>\r\n<p>VIMMI was founded by visionaries who foresaw the multi-platform, anywhere, anytime video future and were committed to making that future easily accessible to any content owner, service provider, enterprise or public organization. It has designed a suite of video services that empower content owners and operators to fully monetize their video assets. These services include the VIMMI global video Content Delivery Network (CDN), in-cloud content preparation services, a modular in-cloud Back Office & Video Monetization Suite and a ready-to-use OTT-as-a-service solution. Other notable clients include Israel based telecom operator Pelephone and wireless networks company Cellcom.\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>About VIASAT</h4>\r\n<p>ViaSat is a direct broadcast satellite television distributor and was founded as Vision TV in 2006. Better known as ViaSat Ukraine, it is based in Kiev, Ukraine. As of September 10, 2007, ViaSat Ukraine operates as a subsidiary of Modern Times Group MTG AB and Strong Media Group, Ltd. and became the first operator in Ukraine’s history to receive a license as a satellite provider of Program Services. Since April 21, 2008, Ukrainian TV viewers are able to enjoy a wide variety of quality TV programming brought to them under the well-known ViaSat brand.</p></script>', 'VIMMI Media Delivery Platform helps ViaSat Drive Higher Revenues with Launch of new Internet TV Service', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2427-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-15 20:55:30', '2017-02-15 20:55:30', '', 2427, 'http://vimmi.loc/2427-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3902, 1, '2017-02-15 20:55:36', '2017-02-15 20:55:36', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Integration enables Vimmi to provide it’s end-to-end Online Video Platform powered by V-Nova PERSEUS™ technology</li>\r\n	<li>Combination of best-in-class PERSEUS compression with Vimmi’s edge processing and machine learning CDN technologies provides an unmatched reduction in video delivery costs</li>\r\n	<li>Pre-integration with all-inclusive modular OTT workflow enables the launch of PERSEUS-enabled online video services in minimum time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>London, September 1, 2016</strong> - <a href="http://www.v-nova.com/en/index.html">V-Nova Ltd.</a>, a global software IP company that delivers game-changing video and data encoding solutions, and Vimmi, the technology leader in distributed video delivery network platforms, today announced that V-Nova PERSEUS™ video compression has been integrated within the Vimmi video delivery platform.\r\n\r\nThe integration represents a major milestone in enabling the launch of PERSEUS-powered online video services in a matter of days. The pre-integrated OTT workflow includes transcoding, content management (CMS), subscriber management (SMS), billing, CDN, DRM, nDVR, HTML5 video player, STB and mobile applications.\r\n\r\n“V-Nova’s smart new way of compressing video integrates with our OVP platform and machine learning CDN architecture to provide a step-change in video transport performance,” said Eitan Koter, Co. CEO and Founder, Vimmi. “As video streaming continues to mature and becomes significantly more important to any service providers’ business, operators will be looking for the best-in-class technologies that can give them an edge. I believe the V-Nova and Vimmi collaboration is going to be provide them with exactly that solution through the combination of the highest possible video delivery efficiency with low cost and fast deployment.”\r\n\r\nVimmi has designed a suite of video services that empower content owners and operators to fully monetise their video assets. These services include the Vimmi Content Delivery Network (CDN), in-cloud content preparation services, a modular in-cloud Back Office &amp; Video Monetization Suite and a ready-to-use OTT-as-a-service solution.\r\n\r\nV-Nova PERSEUS is a video processing technology that addresses today’s video delivery challenges. V-Nova PERSEUS redraws the traditional quality-bitrate curve, enabling operators and service providers to provide high quality live and on-demand video within their bandwidth constraints. V-Nova PERSEUS technology is available as a software development kit (SDK) for integration into third party encoders and video players.\r\n\r\n“We have shown that PERSEUS compression technology can make a real difference to the cost-base and business success of OTT platforms. The integration with Vimmi makes it even more effective: by combining it with an advanced CDN technology and a fully functional, modular video platform ready to deploy in minimum time,” said Guido Meardi, CEO and co-founder of V-Nova. “Vimmi and V-Nova are natural partners, both providing real innovation for operators distributing and monetizing video. Thanks to the work we have done together in record time, it is now easier than ever to deploy our video compression solutions making it clearer than ever why it simply has to be PERSEUS for OTT video delivery.”\r\n\r\nThe joint solution, which is commercially deployable now, will launch at IBC, with live demos on the Vimmi (3.B56) and V-Nova (14.K17) IBC stands.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note to editors:</strong>\r\nIf you would like to meet V-Nova at IBC, please e-mail\r\n<a href="mailto:v-nova@platformpr.com">v-nova@platformpr.com</a>, or call Platform’s Sophie Kay, on +44 207 486 4900.\r\n\r\nTo meet Vimmi at IBC, please email <a href="mailto:sales@vimmi.loc">sales@vimmi.loc</a> or call +972 77 407 4020\r\n<h3>About V-Nova</h3>\r\nV-Nova is a London-headquartered software company providing advanced signal compression technology and software solutions to address the dramatic growth in global network traffic. V-Nova is at the heart of digitalisation, serving multiple industry segments, including TV &amp; Media where it provides solutions spanning the entire media delivery chain, from UHD/4K contribution to distribution, to connected devices and set-top-boxes.\r\n\r\nV-Nova''s award-winning PERSEUS™ technology closes the gap between evolving capacity needs and limitations associated with legacy compression technologies to process data and video in new ways. This means that data can be transported, stored and secured, faster and more cost-effectively, without the need for network upgrades. V-Nova is driving a new era in TV &amp; Media with ground-breaking software solutions that shift the bitrate-quality curve to enable UHD at HD bitrates, HD at SD bitrates, and SD video at sub-audio bitrates.\r\n\r\nV-Nova is empowering a growing number of customers and partners to differentiate their products, increase market reach, and provide new services, all within currently available bandwidth and infrastructure.\r\n\r\nFor more information please visit <a href="http://www.v-nova.com">www.v-nova.com</a>\r\n<h3>About Vimmi</h3>\r\nVimmi was founded by visionaries who foresaw the multi-platform, anywhere, anytime video future and were committed to making that future easily accessible to any content owner, service provider, enterprise or public organization.\r\nVimmi is realizing its mission with innovative, comprehensive built-for-video network architecture technologies that provide cloud-based video services and broadcast-quality delivery services across managed and unmanaged networks. Vimmi enables its customers to reach any screen, at any time, with any content from any location in the world and to maximise return on their valuable video assets.\r\n<h3>For more information, contact:</h3>\r\nV-Nova Ltd.\r\nOne Sheldon Square\r\nLondon W2 6TT, UK.\r\npress@v-nova.com\r\n+44 (20) 7046 6270\r\n<a href="http://www