(4213, 1, '2017-03-17 10:46:59', '2017-03-17 10:46:59', '[spb_row parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" row_overlay_opacity="0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/2" el_position="first"]\r\n\r\nOperational analytics: The key to service assurance and consumer experience management\r\n\r\nWith increasing use of video, constant <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #333;" href="https://edit-my-paper.net/grade-my-paper/">grade-my-paper/</a> data streams, and soaring customer expectations, operators and content providers are living in a very <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #333;" href="https://essaywritingservicehelp.co.uk/proofreading/">proofreading</a> precarious world, with customers ready to jump ship at the first sight of trouble. Price wars are also driving down profits, meaning that Quality of Service (QoS) is increasingly critical to differentiation in a crowded market. Gone are the days when operators simply needed to provide reliable video services and quality content; now, data is king. A transformational shift in service assurance has become crucial to competitiveness.\r\n\r\nNetwork failures and service degradation have a huge impact on profits, productivity and reputation. In today’s world of social media, the voice of one unhappy customer travels far, so problems must be fixed quickly. Yet a lack of real-time visibility into network operations is hindering operators’ ability to act, and means that they’re unable to effectively manage costs in their environment. This impacts directly on profits as Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) rockets. To remain competitive, operators need to find a way of driving down costs, while improving QoS.\r\n\r\nVimmi analytics and reporting tools enables operators and content providers to access critical real time traffic and usage information broken out by region, node, account, request, video stream, viewing model (VOD/live/playlist) and platform. The system provides all information needed to optimize resource utilization, traffic patterns and account policies.\r\n\r\nReporting on CDN historical performance and trends is based on data from monitoring systems and the CDN core. Parameters include storage utilization, service availability and load. Operators may monitor and manage log processing and track object distribution statistics. Information about all internal processes is presented clearly, enabling operators to keep constant tabs on system performance.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_single_image image="2039" image_size="full" frame="noframe" intro_animation="flip" full_width="no" lightbox="yes" link_target="_self" width="1/2" el_position="last"] [/spb_row] [blank_spacer height="30px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]', 'Analytics and Reporting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '501-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-17 10:46:59', '2017-03-17 10:46:59', '', 501, 'http://vimmi.loc/501-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4214, 1, '2017-03-17 10:49:31', '2017-03-17 10:49:31', '[spb_row parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" row_overlay_opacity="0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n\r\nThe Billing module provides a user interface that allows customers to register accounts, view and update account details, check bills and review past activity. Through the billing system, customers can sign up for email-delivery of bills and activate accounts on PCs, IPTV and mobile devices. The billing system also includes mobile apps that can be downloaded for free and enable customers to purchase from the video store or register for operator service directly from a mobile device. Billing for the app may be managed through Google or iTunes app stores or directly via the billing system.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_row] [blank_spacer height="30px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]', 'Billing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '455-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-17 10:49:31', '2017-03-17 10:49:31', '', 455, 'http://vimmi.loc/455-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4215, 1, '2017-03-17 10:52:15', '2017-03-17 10:52:15', '[boxed_content type="coloured" custom_bg_colour="#ffffff" custom_text_colour="#000000" pb_margin_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<h4 class="spb-heading">Campaign and Affiliate Management</h4>\r\nFor affiliate marketing, the Vimmi Monetization Suite provides a complete cloud-based platform for cross-promotion, cross-selling and revenue sharing. The affiliate marketing module provides sophisticated tools for creating and refining highly effective integrated campaigns and packages and for allocating revenues to affiliate program partners.\r\n\r\nCreate a range of viewing destinations to generate greatest returns on your content\r\nPublish videos to more websites by invisibly overlaying the Vimmi player on a partner or affiliate''s player\r\nControl your content with management tools including a variety of account authorizations\r\nPowerful analytics integrated in Vimmi embedded players provide viewer response data even when content is viewed on affiliate sites\r\nBoost content sales by enabling viewers to purchase content via the Vimmi content player that is embedded on partner and affiliate websites.\r\n\r\n[/boxed_content] [blank_spacer height="30px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]', 'Campain & Affiliate Mamagement', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '464-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-17 10:52:15', '2017-03-17 10:52:15', '', 464, 'http://vimmi.loc/464-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4216, 1, '2017-03-17 10:53:22', '2017-03-17 10:53:22', '[spb_row parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" row_overlay_opacity="0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<h3><a href="http://vimmi.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/inner_page_monetization.png"><img class=" size-full wp-image-458 aligncenter" src="http://vimmi.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/inner_page_monetization.png" alt="inner_page_monetization" width="924" height="178" /></a></h3>\r\n<h3>GLOBAL VIDEO CDN</h3>\r\nThe VIMMI CDN video delivery network is designed to quickly and reliably deliver flawless SD and HD Adaptive Bit Rate (ABR) video to any screen or device, worldwide, over unmanaged IP networks. It provides an exceptional customer experience by reducing the amount of traffic that must be transferred between the origin point and an ISP over what are usually low bandwidth links. VIMMI ensures high stream quality even when bandwidth is relatively low.\r\n\r\nVIMMI enables operators and content owners to rapidly scale their CDN capacity to reach an unlimited number of viewers, everywhere, around the globe.\r\n\r\nThe CDN effortlessly handles all video formats and profiles. Its streaming servers offer exceptional traffic throughput and consumer connection support. Advanced distributed storage technology provides outstanding reliability and quality of service across any geographical span. As an open platform, all system elements use APIs to make setup and integration with the customer environment fast and simple.\r\n\r\nVIMMI professionally-staffed NOC stands behind up its highly resilient, reliable CDN. The NOC is available to help at any time, day or night, every day of the year, 24x7x365.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/16">VIMMI Global Network</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/17">VIMMI Global Network Operations Center</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/18">CDN Management System</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/19">Live streaming</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/24">VOD streaming and personalization</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/30">Mobile Video Delivery</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/31">Analytics and reporting</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://vimmi.loc/node/32">Advanced, customizable video player for PCs</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_row]', 'CDN', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '485-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-17 10:53:22', '2017-03-17 10:53:22', '', 485, 'http://vimmi.loc/485-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4217, 1, '2017-03-17 10:54:52', '2017-03-17 10:54:52', '[spb_row parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" row_overlay_opacity="0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_single_image image="1261" image_size="medium" frame="noframe" intro_animation="flip" full_width="no" lightbox="yes" link_target="_self" width="1/4" el_position="first"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="3/4" el_position="last"]\r\n<h3 style="text-align: left;">CDN MANAGEMENT SYSTEM</h3>\r\nThe VIMMI web-based portal is an integrated operations management center that serves as a single entry point for managing and monitoring CDN features and performance. It enables you to control your CDN from any location, yet is remarkably intuitive and user-friendly.\r\n\r\nVia the operations center, you can manage, cluster and monitor all CDN nodes and services, and add new ones as needed. Account provisioning capabilities enable administrators to define and configure accounts by assigning server and storage resources and specifying performance policies and parameters. Nodes and other resources may be designated as dedicated or shared, and policies may be defined for individual accounts or account classes.\r\n\r\nCDN operators can set policies, manage and optimize networks on a regional/geographic basis as well as by account, all from a single NOC screen. Delivery nodes and clusters may be linked to specific regions. Changes are registered and become effective immediately.\r\n\r\nThe management platform includes an analytics and reporting system that provides critical real time usage information for optimizing resource utilization, CDN traffic patterns and account policies.\r\n\r\nHistorical performance reports cover storage utilization, service availability and load. Operators may monitor and manage log processing and track object distribution statistics. Information about all internal processes is presented clearly, enabling operators to keep close tabs on system performance.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_row]', 'CDN MANAGEMENT SYSTEM', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '218-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-17 10:54:52', '2017-03-17 10:54:52', '', 218, 'http://vimmi.loc/218-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4218, 1, '2017-03-17 10:57:56', '2017-03-17 10:57:56', '[spb_row wrap_type="content-width" parallax_type="image" bg_image="1021" bg_type="cover" parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.2" row_overlay_opacity="0" row_padding_vertical="30" row_margin_vertical="30" remove_element_spacing="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [blank_spacer height="100px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<h1 class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll  " style="text-align: center;">The VIMMI Video Monetization System (VMS) is a modular suite of in-cloud services that enables content owners and service providers to effectively manage and market their content to current and potential partners and customers, and maximize market share and ARPU.</h1>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [blank_spacer height="100px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [/spb_row] [spb_row wrap_type="content-width" row_bg_color="#eaf4f6" parallax_type="color" bg_type="cover" parallax_video_height="video-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" row_overlay_opacity="0" row_padding_vertical="0" row_margin_vertical="0" remove_element_spacing="no" row_el_class="full-wid" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="3/4" el_position="first"]\r\n\r\n<span class="animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-h1">VIDEO STORE</span>\r\n<p class="  animated fadeInDown eds-on-scroll fall-p1 ">The VIMMI Video Store enables you to quickly create a branded, cross-device, full-service solution for merchandising and delivering video</p>\r\n[sf_button colour="accent" type="stroke-to-fill" size="large" link="http://vimmi.loc/?page_id=443" target="_blank" icon="" dropshad